cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you reference this work, please cite it as below."
title: "prism42-nemotron-med: a sovereign NVIDIA medical-LLM stack on Brev Hopper GPUs"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Dent
    given-names: Brandon
    name-suffix: MD
    affiliation: GOATnote
    email: b@thegoatnote.com
  - name: "prism42 contributors"
date-released: "2026-04-28"
url: "https://github.com/GOATnote-Inc/prism42/pull/11"
repository-code: "https://github.com/GOATnote-Inc/prism42/tree/nemotron-med-hackathon/mvp/nemotron-med"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - "medical large language models"
  - "NVIDIA Nemotron"
  - "sovereign inference"
  - "HealthBench"
  - "knowledge graph retrieval"
  - "Hopper"
  - "TensorRT-LLM"
  - "vLLM"
  - "NeMo Guardrails"
abstract: >-
  prism42-nemotron-med is a sovereign NVIDIA medical-LLM stack that serves
  Nemotron-3 on Brev Hopper GPUs and benchmarks against HealthBench Hard
  with a sovereign judge — no cloud LLM API keys in any code path. The lane
  is air-gapped from the prism42 production voice surface; isolation is
  enforced via pre-commit hooks and per-commit production-page hash diffs.
